rovided the theme for  Milton's  poetic drama Samson Agonistes (  1671 ), which is modelled on ancient Greek tragedy. In the Middle Ages the popularity of the given name was increased in Celtic areas by the fame of a 6th-century Celtic saint who bore it, probably as a classicized form of some ancient Celtic name. He was a Welsh monk who did missionary work in Cornwall and afterwards established a monastery at Dol in Brittany."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Samson Wasseborne II was born in 1142, in Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Samson Wasseborne II. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"1142–":"1142–Surnud","1141–Male":"1141–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1142–Female":"1142–Surnud","1142":"1142","1141":"1141","Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1142–":"1142–Kuollut","1141–Male":"1141–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1142–Female":"1142–Kuollut","1142":"1142","1141":"1141","Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1142–":"1142–Décédée","1141–Male":"1141–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1142–Female":"1142–Décédée","1142":"1142","1141":"1141","Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Samson Wasseborne II est née en 1142, à Worcestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Samson Wasseborne II. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"1142–":"1142–Verstorben","1141–Male":"1141–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1142–Female":"1142–Verstorben","1142":"1142","1141":"1141","Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Samson Wasseborne II wurde 1142 in Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit Samson Wasseborne II mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb in ihrem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1142–":"1142–Desede","1141–Male":"1141–Desede","–Male":"Desede","1142–Female":"1142–Desede","1142":"1142","11